
This is a gold standard test set for evaluating terminology translation in MT.
This test set was created from a English--Hindi legal domain data (i.e. proceedings of legal judgments). 
The gold standard test set is a part of the IIT Bombay English-Hindi parallel corpus (Kunchukuttan et al., 2017), 
and contains 1,270 sentence-pairs. 


It includes two sentence-aligned text files. English: term-tagged-aligned-1270.en, and Hindi: term-tagged-aligned-1270.hi. Each line of the term-tagged-aligned-1270.* files has three fields separated by "|||", which are:

1. English/Hindi sentences |||
2. List of legal terms appearing in the sentences (separated by "|"), and terms' lexical and inflectional variations (if any), and term IDs |||
3. Term ID: start - end positions of each term in sentence  

As an example, we show a pair of English--Hindi (term annotated and aligned) sentences from the gold standard test set below.

ENGLISH:
acts of negligence , errors of judgment , or innocent mistake , do not constitute such misconduct . ||| trm1:acts of negligence:acts of carelessness|trm2:errors of judgment:errors of adjudication:errors of decision:errors of judgement:errors of pronouncement:errors of verdict|trm3:innocent mistake:guiltless mistake:harmless mistake:sinless mistake:unoffending mistake|trm4:misconduct:abuse:malpractice:misuse| ||| 1:0-2 2:4-6 3:9-10 4:16-16 

HINDI:
लापरवाही के कृत्य , न्याय की त्रुटियां , अहानिकर ग़लती , इस तरह का कदाचार नहीं होते हैं . ||| trm1:लापरवाही के कृत्य:उपेक्षा के कृत्य|trm2:न्याय की त्रुटियां:अधिनिर्णय की गलतियां:अधिनिर्णय की त्रुटियां:निर्णय की गलतियां:निर्णय की त्रुटियां:निर्णयादेश की गलतियां:निर्णयादेश की त्रुटियां:न्याय की गलतियां:न्यायनिर्णय की गलतियां:न्यायनिर्णय की त्रुटियां:पंचाट की गलतियां:पंचाट की त्रुटियां:फैसला की गलतियां:फैसला की त्रुटियां:राय की गलतियां:राय की त्रुटियां:विचार की गलतियां:विचार की त्रुटियां|trm3:अहानिकर ग़लती:अहानिकर गलती:अहानिकर भूल|trm4:कदाचार:अवचार:दुराचार:अनैतिकता:क़सूर| ||| 1:0-2 2:4-6 3:8-9 4:14-14

Please cite the following paper if you use this data set for your experiments.


Rejwanul Haque, Mohammed Hasanuzzaman and Andy Way (2019). Investigating Terminology Translation in Statistical and Neural Machine Translation: A Case Study on English-to-Hindi and Hindi-to-English. In Proceedings of RANLP 2019: Recent Advances in Natural Language Processing, pp. 437--446, Varna, Bulgaria. 

